  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the rice, 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span>&nbsp;water to a large pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, cut the pak choi in half, separating the white and green parts</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cut</strong> the white part into bite-size pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Shred</strong> the green tops&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Heat</strong> a large, dry wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> hot, add the white pak choi (keep the shredded green part for later) with a pinch of salt</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cook</strong> for 3-4 min or until starting to colour&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, slice the spring onions finely, discarding the root ends</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Peel</strong> the ginger (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once </strong>the rice is cooked, transfer the pak choi to the same pot, without stirring</p>\r\n<p>Tip: if the rice needs a little longer, then just wait until it's finished cooking before adding the pak choi</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cover </strong>the cooked rice and pak choi with a lid&nbsp;to keep warm until serving&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Combine</strong> the ginger, chilli jam, rice vinegar and soy sauce with 50ml<span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;[100ml]</span>&nbsp;water&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>This</strong> is your sweet chilli sauce&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/577.-step--5-x700.jpg",
